# Trivy ignore list — controlled via PR review.
#
# Each entry MUST include:
#   - CVE id
#   - one-line reason for ignoring (e.g. "false positive: package not used at runtime",
#     "fix pending upstream, mitigated by NetworkPolicy", "vulnerable code path
#     unreachable")
#   - link to the PR that added it
#
# Example:
# CVE-2024-XXXXX  # not exploitable: only loaded in test env (#42)

# ---- Phase 2.5 initial baseline (PR #3) ----
# All three are unreachable at runtime; follow-up issue: clean builder leftovers + bump distroless.

# libpython3.11-minimal DoS via http.client — we don't use http.client (httpx instead).
# Fixed in 3.11.2-6+deb12u7; will pick up via next distroless `:nonroot` rebuild.
CVE-2025-13836

# jaraco.context — pulled in by setuptools as a transitive build-time dep; not invoked at runtime.
CVE-2026-23949

# wheel — pip/uv build-time dep; runtime never installs packages.
CVE-2026-24049

# ---- Phase 11 follow-up ----
# krb5 (libgssapi-krb5-2 / libk5crypto3 / libkrb5-3 / libkrb5support0) DoS via
# integer overflow. Comes from the distroless debian-12 base, NOT our deps.
# Unreachable: this service uses no Kerberos/GSSAPI (Postgres = password auth,
# providers = HTTPS). distroless has no apt to patch in place; fixed upstream in
# 1.20.1-2+deb12u5 — will clear via the next distroless `:nonroot` rebuild.
CVE-2026-40356
